The paper proposes a deep learning model for passenger demand prediction, which involves complex interactions among spatial and temporal factors and external factors such as weather. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to machine learning, artificial intelligence, computer vision, and neural networks. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper proposes an end-to-end learning framework with different neural networks modeling different factors. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper deals with complex interactions and uncertainty in data. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible category as the paper uses a convolutional long short-term memory network to capture spatio-temporal feature interactions. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper proposes a novel feature fusion method with a convolution operation and an attention layer. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with passenger demand prediction, which could be related to social networks and information networks.
